Subject: [PATCH AP-04] vmnet: inject vm_check_build macro into Makefile.kernel

vmnet's Makefile.kernel uses $(call vm_check_build, ...) to detect kernel API
availability at compile time. However, vm_check_build is defined only in
Makefile.normal (used for direct `make` invocations) and is NOT present in
Makefile.kernel (used by the kernel kbuild system).

When kbuild calls Makefile.kernel, any $(call vm_check_build, ...) expression
silently expands to an empty string, disabling the feature detection without
any error or warning. This causes compile-time checks to be silently skipped
and capabilities like VMW_NETIF_TRANS_UPDATE or VMW_NETIF_SINGLE_NAPI_PARM
to never be set.

This patch injects the vm_check_build definition into Makefile.kernel so that
feature-detection calls work correctly under kbuild.

Applied by: _autopatch_vmcheck_build() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  Always applied when vm_check_build is referenced but not defined

---
 vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel b/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
--- a/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
+++ b/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
@@ -20,6 +20,11 @@ INCLUDE := -I$(SRCROOT)
 
 ccflags-y := $(CC_OPTS) $(INCLUDE)
+
+# vm_check_build: compile-test a C snippet; yields flag2 on success, flag3 on error
+vm_check_build = $(shell if $(CC) $(ccflags-y) -Werror -S -o /dev/null -xc $(1) \
+    > /dev/null 2>&1; then echo "$(2)"; else echo "$(3)"; fi)
+
 ccflags-y += $(call vm_check_build, $(SRCROOT)/netif_trans_update.c,-DVMW_NETIF_TRANS_UPDATE, )
